rders of the DVM-500Plus In-Car Video System will now include the VoiceVault™ Advanced Wireless Microphone at no additional cost to the customer. Previously only available with the DVM-750 In-Car Video System, the VoiceVault offers the same extended range, voice optimization and noise filtering, and fully digital audio transmission with true frequency hopping technology as the previous DVM-500Plus system’s mic. However, it also offers the industry-first feature of recording up to two hours of audio evidence onto On-Board Solid State Memory when the mic is out of range or the signal to the in-car video system is interrupted. The VoiceVault also records its own metadata to later link with recordings from the in-car video system for the same incidents when loaded into Digital Ally’s VideoManager software.		 Web: http://www.digitalallyinc.com  DVM-750 Released by Digital Ally Inc in November 2011    		At this year’s IACP Conference, Digital Ally, Inc. is introducing new software that allows a MDT or MDC to control the DVM-750 In-Car Video System. The MDC-750 Interface Software provides full control of the DVM-750 In-Car Video System via Touch Screen (easy to use, graphical on-screen buttons) or Keyboard Interface. This includes user and password entry, recording, audio controls, camera selection, zooming, event marking, playback, metadata display, menu access, and more. If the MDT/MDC running the application fails or the cable to the DVM-750 is unplugged, the video system buttons will become active to allow normal operation.		 Web: http://www.digitalallyinc.com/  Digital Ally DVM-750 In-Car Video System Released by Digital Ally Inc in May 2011    		DVM-750 In-Car Video Systems can now be updated and configured wirelessly. Customers may use a laptop/MDC or compact module for wireless transfer. Interactive maps of routes travelled in the recordings are also now available in VideoManagerII.		 Web: http://www.digitalallyinc.com  Digital Ally VideoManager Software Released by Digital Ally Inc in April 2011    		Digital Ally added a new tool to its VideoManager software to track the location of video taken with its GPS-enabled units. It now includes a feature that utilizes an in-program overhead map to view routes traversed in videos along with the location of "marked" events. This feature gives officers an easy-to-read interface for pinpointing the location of where recorded video was created.		 Web: http://www.digitalallyinc.com  Digital Ally VoiceVault MIC Released by Digital Ally Inc in October 2010    		Digital Ally’s VoiceVault™ MIC includes industry-first features like On-Board Memory to record when out of the 1-mile max range. An earpiece allows officer communication or listening to suspects. It includes integrated GPS with event marking, it embeds coordinates and date / time stamp, it has an emergency call feature and more.		 Web: http://www.digitalallyinc.com 
